cnt2Transport.name: cnt2Transport
cnt2Transport.contactinfo: Computer Network Technology Technical Support 6000 Nathan Lane North Plymouth, Minnesota 55442 telephone: (763) 268-6000 fax: (763) 268-6800 support: 1-800-NET-TECH
cnt2Transport.description: This defines the CNT Transport MIB. The Transport layer provides network link for CNT proprietary traffic.

cnt2TransportTable.name: cnt2TransportTable
cnt2TransportTable.description: A list of Transport network link entries.

cnt2TransportSlotIndex.name: cnt2TransportSlotIndex
cnt2TransportSlotIndex.description: The slot index for this Transport entry

cnt2TransportIndex.name: cnt2TransportIndex
cnt2TransportIndex.description: The relative index of the bus number in this Transport entry

cnt2TransportVid.name: cnt2TransportVid
cnt2TransportVid.description: The virtual circuit number VCI. If ATM is used, make sure this Vid is configured the same as the VCI. Failure to do so will cause unexpected results

cnt2TransportLinkType.name: cnt2TransportLinkType
cnt2TransportLinkType.description: The Link type supported by the CNT Transport layer.

cnt2TransportLinkDesc.name: cnt2TransportLinkDesc
cnt2TransportLinkDesc.description: The description of the network link suported by the CNT Transport layer

cnt2TransportLinkStatus.name: cnt2TransportLinkStatus
cnt2TransportLinkStatus.description: The network link's status. The link status indicates if there is communication between the local node and the remote node.

cnt2TransportIPtosPrecedence.name: cnt2TransportIPtosPrecedence
cnt2TransportIPtosPrecedence.description: The service precedence of IP Type of Service use by this link. There is an 8 bit field in an IP datagram that specifies the type of service a datagram is requesting (or hinting). It may then be used by the network to determine paths and precedence for a given datagram. The specific bits used may vary depending on the network (see RFC 791 for more details). The IpServiceType attribute can be used on a per circuit basis to specify the bits to be set in the IP datagram's service type field. Each Transport IP datagram destined for the DestionationIpAddress will have this field set. This attributes only applicable to IP providers. The service precedence is in bit 0-2 of the 8 bit IP Type of Service field.

cnt2TransportIPtosDelay.name: cnt2TransportIPtosDelay
cnt2TransportIPtosDelay.description: The IP Type of Service Delay option use by this link. The Delay bit is in bit 3 of the 8 bit IP Type of Service field.

cnt2TransportIPtosThruput.name: cnt2TransportIPtosThruput
cnt2TransportIPtosThruput.description: The IP Type of Service Throughput option use by this link. The Throughput bit is in bit 4 of the 8 bit IP Type of Service field.

cnt2TransportIPtosRelibility.name: cnt2TransportIPtosRelibility
cnt2TransportIPtosRelibility.description: The IP Type of Service Relibility option use by this link. The Relibility bit is in bit 5 of the 8 bit IP Type of Service field.

cnt2TransportRemoteIp.name: cnt2TransportRemoteIp
cnt2TransportRemoteIp.description: The remote IP address. This address is set when Transport is configured.

cnt2TransportProtocol.name: cnt2TransportProtocol
cnt2TransportProtocol.description: The protocol used by this link. At the moment the only protocol is SAP.

cnt2TransportCompressionOption.name: cnt2TransportCompressionOption
cnt2TransportCompressionOption.description: Reflects whether compression option is turned on/off.

cnt2TransportMaxXmitRate.name: cnt2TransportMaxXmitRate
cnt2TransportMaxXmitRate.description: The Maximum Transfer Rate of this link.

cnt2TransportResetTime.name: cnt2TransportResetTime
cnt2TransportResetTime.description: The time, in seconds, when the stats was last reset.

cnt2TransportInPkts.name: cnt2TransportInPkts
cnt2TransportInPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted to the link

cnt2TransportInOctets.name: cnt2TransportInOctets
cnt2TransportInOctets.description: The number of bytes transmitted to the link

cnt2TransportOutPkts.name: cnt2TransportOutPkts
cnt2TransportOutPkts.description: The number of packets transmitted out from the link

cnt2TransportOutOctets.name: cnt2TransportOutOctets
cnt2TransportOutOctets.description: The number of bytes transmitted out from the link

cnt2TransportRexmit.name: cnt2TransportRexmit
cnt2TransportRexmit.description: The number of packets being retransmitted

cnt2TransportOosHigh.name: cnt2TransportOosHigh
cnt2TransportOosHigh.description: The number of out of sequence packets received

cnt2TransportStatsReset.name: cnt2TransportStatsReset
cnt2TransportStatsReset.description: Setting this will result the Transport statistic to be reset

cnt2TransportRawOutOctets.name: cnt2TransportRawOutOctets
cnt2TransportRawOutOctets.description: The number of bytes transmitted out from the lower interface of Transport layer. This is the amount of data after Compression plus Transport header.

cnt2TransportRawInOctets.name: cnt2TransportRawInOctets
cnt2TransportRawInOctets.description: The number of bytes received in from the lower interface of Transport layer. This is the amount of data after Compression plus Transport header.

cnt2TransportWindowSize.name: cnt2TransportWindowSize
cnt2TransportWindowSize.description: The current window size, value is number buffers outstanding on the connection

cnt2TransportSegmentSize.name: cnt2TransportSegmentSize
cnt2TransportSegmentSize.description: Range from (0 to 65532) If this value is non-zero, this value is used for segmentation. If equal to 0, then TransportSegmentSizeHi is what being used.

cnt2TransportSegmentSizeHi.name: cnt2TransportSegmentSizeHi
cnt2TransportSegmentSizeHi.description: Range from (0 to 65532) If this value is used when TransportSegmentSize is set to 0. This value is passed in from user layer's MTU size.

cnt2TransportRoundTripTimer.name: cnt2TransportRoundTripTimer
cnt2TransportRoundTripTimer.description: The current round trip timer. each count is in 50msec.

cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio1.name: cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio1
cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio1.description: Incremented when an ack is received and there is no data on the hold queue and there is no outstanding (unacked) data. It indicates that transmission is idled until more data is received from the user.

cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio2.name: cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio2
cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio2.description: Incremented when an ack is received and there is no data on the hold queue but there is outstanding (unacked) data.

cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio3.name: cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio3
cnt2TransportHoldCountRatio3.description: Incremented when an ack is received and there is data on the hold queue ready to be sent.
